questionListItems.title: Do I need to be a Community Health Assist Scheme (CHAS) cardholder to enjoy the New Healthier SG Chronic Tier under Healthier SG from 2024?

answer.body: You will need to be a CHAS/ Pioneer Generation (PG)/ Merdeka Generation (MG) cardholder and also be enrolled with a Healthier SG GP clinic to be eligible for the subsidies under the new Healthier SG Chronic Tier, which will be available from early 2024 onwards. Under this Healthier SG Chronic Tier, these CHAS/PG/MG patients, especially those with high medication needs, can opt for and benefit from this alternative subsidy tier, allowing them to enjoy common chronic drugs from their enrolled Healthier SG GP clinics at prices comparable to polyclinics. You or your household members can sign up at  www.chas.sg.

questionListItems.title: Is there a step-by-step guide for enrolling in Healthier SG?

answer.body:
Two ways you can enrol in Healthier SG:

 

1) Enrol in Healthier SG via HealthHub

  • Eligible residents will receive an SMS invitation from MOH to enrol.

  • If you don't already have the HealthHub app, download the app from Google Play or Apple App Store.

  • Login to HealthHub using Singpass and click on Healthier SG banner.

  • Select your user profile. 

  • Click on ‘Enrol to Healthier SG’ button.

  • Choose your preferred Healthier SG clinic and make an appointment for your first Health Plan consultation.

  • Complete an Onboarding Questionnaire before you see your doctor.


2) Alternatively, you may approach our Healthier SG Ambassadors at Enrolment Stations (see https://gowhere.gov.sg/healthiersg for locations) for assistance.

questionListItems.title: How do I book my first appointment for my Health Plan discussion?

answer.body:
Follow the steps below to book your first consultation with your enrolled Healthier SG clinic for your health plan discussion:


Step 1:

  • Access your HealthHub app and log in with your Singpass.

  • Click on the Healthier SG banner in green on the homepage or select 'Healthier SG' in the Service Categories page.


Step 2:

  • Follow the instructions within the app to enrol in Healthier SG.


Step 3:

  • After enrolment, you will be prompted to the 'Book appointment' screen.

  • Alternatively, in the Health Recommendations main page, click on 'Manage appointment' to schedule a consultation with your enrolled clinic.


After which, you will be able to book an appointment via:

  • an in-app booking system;

  • email your contact details to the clinic; or

  • call the clinic via their contact number provided.

questionListItems.title: What are the chronic conditions covered under Healthier SG Chronic Tier?

answer.body:
Enrolees with any chronic conditions under the Chronic Disease Management Programme (CDMP) and have CHAS/Merdeka Generation/Pioneer Generation cards can opt for the Healthier SG Chronic Tier, which allows them access to common chronic drugs at prices comparable to polyclinics. The chronic conditions under CDMP are:


  • Diabetes Mellitus/ Pre-diabetes

  • Hypertension

  • Hyperlipidaemia (Lipid Disorders)

  • Stroke

  • Asthma

  • Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD)

  • Schizophrenia

  • Major Depression

  • Bipolar Disorder

  • Dementia

  • Osteoarthritis

  • Benign Prostatic Hyperplasia

  • Anxiety

  • Parkinson's Disease

  • Chronic Kidney Disease (Nephrosis/Nephritis)

  • Epilepsy

  • Osteoporosis

  • Psoriasis

  • Rheumatoid Arthritis

  • Ischaemic Heart Disease

  • Allergic Rhinitis

  • Gout

  • Chronic Hepatitis B


For more information, please visit MOH | Chronic Disease Management Programme (CDMP)

questionListItems.title: Can I use my next appointment at the GP/Polyclinic for my first Health Plan discussion?

answer.body: If you have enrolled with your existing GP/Polyclinic, you can use your next scheduled appointment as an opportunity to also have your first Health Plan discussion with the doctor. However, please note that there may still be fees charged for consultation and treatment that are unrelated to Healthier SG.

questionListItems.title: Do I have the flexibility to choose a preferred clinic near my residence or workplace?

answer.body:
Residents can choose any clinic that is participating in Healthier SG. This can be a clinic located near your home or workplace or a clinic that you have visited for many years.

Selection of your preferred Healthier SG clinic can be done within the HealthHub app as you enrol in Healthier SG.

Through HealthHub, you will first see up to three clinics which you frequently visit but you can also use the search bar which allows you to choose a family clinic of your preference that is not on the displayed list.

questionListItems.title: How often do I need to visit my Healthier SG clinic?

answer.body:
Your clinic will advise you on your next check-in dates.


Those with chronic conditions will typically require two to four follow-up consultations annually with a doctor. Prevailing subsidies, such as the Community Health Assist Scheme (CHAS), will apply for visits and treatment. The enhanced Healthier SG benefits will apply for residents seeking care from their enrolled clinic.


For those without chronic conditions, you may check-in with your enrolled clinic annually.

questionListItems.title:
Can my family clinic refer me for specialist care? 
Will subsidised referrals made under Healthier SG be subsidised at public Specialist Outpatient Clinics (SOC)?

answer.body:
Yes, your family clinic can refer you for subsidised specialist care if it is clinically appropriate. Your doctor (or the care team) will discuss with you prior to making any referral for specialist care. 


CHAS/MG/PG cardholders can receive subsidised referrals to public SOCs through CHAS clinics, which include their Healthier SG GPs. You will be considered a subsidised patient and will receive care from a team of doctors/dentists. Patients who wish to choose a specific doctor at the SOC will have to pay private rates.


For more information on SOC subsidies, please visit the MOH website or check directly with your Healthier SG GP or the public SOC.

questionListItems.title: Who will manage my clinical referrals after seeing my family clinic?

answer.body:
Your Healthier SG GP clinic's care team will facilitate your referrals to specialist outpatient clinics (SOC) and/or Hospital as part of your care (if required). Do inform your clinic's team if you have a preferred SOC and/or Hospital.


There may be situations where you may be required to provide information or submit documents to complete the referral. Your Healthier SG GP clinic's care team will advise you if you need to fill up documents as part of the referral process.

Healthier SG is a national strategy to transform Singapore's healthcare system to focus more on preventive care to help residents stay healthy, detect health issues early and manage them well. Under Healthier SG, residents will be empowered to take steps to improve their health proactively with the support of their trusted family clinic and community partners.

questionListItems.title: I do not have a mobile phone/smartphone and can't receive SMS. How do I enrol in Healthier SG?

answer.body:
There are a few ways that you can enrol in Healthier SG.

 

1. Assisted enrolment


Approach the Healthier SG Ambassadors at Enrolment Stations for assistance. To check for an enrolment station (and operating hours) near you, see:  www.gowhere.gov.sg/healthiersg

 

2. Enrol with caregiver's assistance


You can grant access to your caregiver/family member/loved one by adding him/her in HealthHub, so he/she can enrol you on your behalf using his/her smartphone. You will need your Singpass account to authorise your caregiver via HealthHub. If you do not have a Singpass account, you may register for Singpass through this website (https://www.singpass.gov.sg/home/ui/register/instructions) or head down to the nearest Singpass counter for assistance, with your caregiver and bring along both your NRICs. For Singpass counter locations, see: https://www.singpass.gov.sg/home/ui/counter-locations.

 

For caregiver enrolment, your caregiver can refer to the step-by-step guide here.

 

3. Via a computer


You can self-enrol via HealthHub at https://www.healthhub.sg/. A Singpass account is required to do so.

 

For any clarification, please call 6325 9220.

questionListItems.title: Are there plans for those aged below 40 years old to be included in Healthier SG?

answer.body:
Our population is ageing rapidly with older age groups more susceptible to co-morbidities and chronic illnesses. As such, Healthier SG enrolment will focus on those aged 40 and above to proactively prevent them from falling ill and delay the deterioration of health. We will consider further expansions after the roll-out has stabilised.

In the meantime, all residents should continue to stay active and live healthily. There are a variety of community programmes available, including:

  • People's Association (PA) activities

  • SportSG ActiveHealth programmes

  • Health Promotion Board's (HPB) National Steps Challenge and Eat, Drink, Shop Healthy Challenge

questionListItems.title: How do I check my Healthier SG enrolment status?

answer.body: You are considered to have successfully enrolled when you are able to view your selected clinic's name under "Your Enrolled Clinic" tab in HealthHub.

questionListItems.title: If I do not have a smartphone, how can I make an appointment?

answer.body:
If your caregiver has enrolled you via the HealthHub app, he/she will be able to book an appointment for you through the same app.


Alternatively, you may approach the nearest Enrolment Station for assistance with the appointment booking. Healthier SG ambassadors at the Enrolment Station will provide you with an appointment card to bring along for your appointment. Subsequently, you will receive a Health Plan Booklet at your Healthier SG clinic to keep track of your appointments and guide you towards achieving your health goals.


For more information on the nearest Enrolment Station: https://gowhere.gov.sg/healthiersg
